<!--
    To build consistent typography styles throughout the app, define and use common text styles here.
    Styles defined here should be used through android:textAppearance attribute.
    Unique TextAppearance styles should not be defined here; instead implement such cases
    in styles.xml or within the View itself.

    To define additional text styles, the naming and hierarchy format should be the following:

        Text.[Color].[Size].[*FamilyItem].[*Style].[*Options]

        * Indicates optional

        - Color:       Text Color (e.g. DarkPrimary, DarkTertiary)
        - Size:        Text Size
        - FamilyItem:      Font FamilyItem (e.g. Condensed, Medium)
        - Style:       Text Style (e.g. Bold, Italic)
        - Options:     Any other styles (e.g. AllCaps)

    Default Colors:
        87%     DarkPrimary
        54%     DarkSecondary
        38%     DarkTertiary

        100%    LightPrimary
        70%     LightSecondary
        50%     LightTertiary

    Default Sizes:
        12sp    Caption
        14sp    Body
        16sp    Subheading
        18sp    Heading
        20sp    Title
        24sp    Headline

-->

